# Firebase Configuration
# Replace these with your actual Firebase project credentials
# Get these from: https://console.firebase.google.com/

VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY=your_api_key_here
VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=your_project_id.firebaseapp.com
VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=your_project_id
VITE_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=your_project_id.appspot.com
VITE_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=your_sender_id
VITE_FIREBASE_APP_ID=your_app_id

# Google Gemini API Configuration with Smart Failover (FREE)
# Get your free API keys from: https://makersuite.google.com/app/apikey
#
# SMART FAILOVER: Configure 1-3 API keys for automatic backup
# - If KEY_1 hits rate limit → automatically switches to KEY_2
# - If KEY_2 hits rate limit → automatically switches to KEY_3
# - Rate-limited keys enter 24-hour cooldown
#
# Rate limits PER KEY (FREE tier):
# - 60 requests/min, 1,500 requests/day, 1M tokens/month
#
# With 3 keys you get:
# - 4,500 requests/day total capacity
# - 3M tokens/month total capacity
# - Automatic failover when limits hit
#
# REQUIRED: At least one key must be configured
VITE_GEMINI_API_KEY=your_first_gemini_api_key_here

# OPTIONAL: Backup keys for higher capacity and automatic failover
VITE_GEMINI_API_KEY_2=your_second_gemini_api_key_here
VITE_GEMINI_API_KEY_3=your_third_gemini_api_key_here

# ModelsLab API Configuration (OPTIONAL - for recipe image generation)
# Get your API key from: https://modelslab.com/
# This is OPTIONAL - only needed if you want AI-generated recipe images
# Comment out if not using
# VITE_MODELSLAB_API_KEY=your_modelslab_api_key_here

# Instructions:
# 1. Go to https://console.firebase.google.com/
# 2. Create a new project or select existing
# 3. Go to Project Settings > General
# 4. Under "Your apps", click Web app (</>) icon
# 5. Register your app and copy the configuration
# 6. Create a new file named ".env" (copy this file)
# 7. Replace the placeholder values with your actual Firebase config
# 8. Enable Email/Password authentication in Firebase Console
# 9. Set up Firestore Database in production mode
# 10. Get 1-3 Gemini API keys from https://makersuite.google.com/app/apikey
#     (Use 3 keys for 3x capacity and automatic failover)

# What Each API Does:
# - Firebase: User authentication, data storage (Firestore), hosting
# - Gemini AI: FREE AI for meal analysis, fridge scanning, smart suggestions
#   * Smart Failover: Automatically switches between keys when rate limited
#   * Configure 1-3 keys for higher capacity (up to 4,500 req/day)
# - ModelsLab: OPTIONAL - generates recipe images (skip if you don't need this)

# Cost Breakdown:
# - Firebase: FREE tier includes generous limits for small apps
# - Gemini AI: 100% FREE per key (60 req/min, 1,500 req/day, 1M tokens/month)
#   * With 3 keys: 4,500 req/day, 3M tokens/month total
# - ModelsLab: OPTIONAL (paid service, not required)
